Reanne Evans, the 10-time ladies' snooker world champion, begins her bid to make history and reach the World Championship finals.

The 29-year-old from Dudley would be the first woman ever to reach The Crucible should she win three qualifiers, but she faces a tough start in the form of 1997 world champion Ken Doherty.

